NOTE: Configurations with SigArc but without PMF are redundant.
      SigArc needs pairs to be stored for the next iterations (PMF),
      otherwise it has no effect.

bit conventions:
without network partitioning: PMF + SigArc + PInvar + 0 + SPartition 

00000 = 0
00001 = 1
00100 = 2
00101 = 3
01000 = 4
01001 = 5
01100 = 6
01101 = 7
10000 = 8
10001 = 9
10100 = 10
10101 = 11
11000 = 12
11001 = 13
11100 = 14
11101 = 15


bit conventions:
with network partitioning: PMF + SigArc + PInvar + NPartition + SPartition 

00000 = 0
00001 = 1
00010 = 2
00011 = 3
00100 = 4
00101 = 5
00110 = 6
00111 = 7
01000 = 8
01001 = 9
01010 = 10
01011 = 11
01100 = 12
01101 = 13
01110 = 14
01111 = 15

10000 = 16
10001 = 17
10010 = 18
10011 = 19
10100 = 20
10101 = 21
10110 = 22
10111 = 23
11000 = 24
11001 = 25
11010 = 26
11011 = 27
11100 = 28
11101 = 29
11110 = 30
11111 = 31
